<plot>This Traveltalks visit to San Francisco starts with views of the San Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge, Golden Gate Bridge, and the Palace of Fine Arts built for the 1915 International Exposition. We then see a performance of the "Cavalcade of the Golden West" that was filmed at the Golden Gate International Exposition. This exposition was held in San Francisco in 1939-1940. The Cavalcade was a stage show that chronicled the growth of the western United States.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?097225</url></doc>
